data.description: This 1,776-square-foot, 3 bedroom, 2.5 bathroom home was built in 1979 on a spacious corner lot in a cul-de-sac in northwest Boise. With plenty of space and mature landscaping, this property has nice privacy in front and back. Off the family room with fireplace are sliding doors to an enormous outdoor concrete patio that runs the length of the house and is covered with a wood trellis. Built-in patio wooden benches provide ample seating area for entertaining. Roof was replaced in October 2020 with 40 year architectural shingles. New living room flooring. All bedrooms are upstairs. Two separate living rooms, formal dining, updated half-bath, and kitchen on the main floor. Attic storage with pull-down stairs. This is a peaceful home in a great neighborhood!
